### [SUB-LEMMA G1] Semantic, measurable definitions of all six parameters

**proof-gap.** The central correctness claim "the parameters control these factors" is vacuous until each of the six factors is a *function on scenarios* whose value the algorithm provably sets. Required: define, for a scenario $\mathcal{S}=(\mathcal{T}_S,\mathcal{A}_S,\mathcal{T}_T,\mathcal{A}_T,\mathcal{M},\mathcal{C})$,
- value-invention $v(\mathcal{S})$ = #labeled nulls in a core universal solution (equiv. #distinct Skolem terms in the restricted chase of $\mathcal{A}_S$ with $\mathcal{M}\cup\mathcal{T}_T$);
- source/target incompleteness $\iota_S,\iota_T$ and correspondence-incompleteness $\kappa$ as *deletion functionals* relative to a closed "complete" baseline;
- cyclicity $\gamma$ as a graph invariant of the mapping dependency graph (e.g. #SCCs containing an existential-marked edge);
- interpretation multiplicity $\mu$ = #pairwise non-$\mathcal{T}_T$-equivalent admissible formalizations of a correspondence.
*Why hard:* $v$ and $\mu$ must be defined semantically (via universal solutions / logical equivalence), not by syntactic counting; otherwise the generator cannot certify the requested values.
